zest /zɛst/

(zests) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Zest is a feeling of pleasure and enthusiasm. 热情 [also 'a' N, oft N 'for' n] 

例： He has a zest for life and a quick intellect. 他有生活的热情和机敏的头脑。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Zest is a quality in an activity or situation which you find exciting. 兴奋点 

例： Live interviews add zest and a touch of the unexpected to any piece of research. 现场采访给任何一份研究增添兴奋点和些许意外。

